    "summary": "As a senior international banker with regional responsibility I have ample experience in the areas of strategic relationship management in Financial Institutions as well as Corporate Clients. Also I have extensive experience in Corporate Credit Risk Analysis, Corporate Credit Risk Restructuring and Compliance/CDD. Using this experience I can be of great help in restoring trust between client and bank, thereby rebuilding profitability within acceptable risk and compliance parameters. \n\n* I have been educated both in Europe and the USA.\n* I have been stationed in Latin America, Asia and Europe.\n* I have succesfully negotiated in over 50 different countries.\n* I have worked at each and every organizational level\n    (branches, regional head office, head office)\n\nPersonal attributes among other are: Common sense, ample strategic insight, good negotiating skills, analytical strength, the ability to improvise and being able to think-out-of-the-box. Also I am service driven, but at the same time result-oriented and skilled in building new activities from scratch, designing new products/services and systems alike. Proper risk management and compliance are key values to me.\n\nSpecialties: \n* Thorough knowledge of (international) banking.\n* Skilled in (high level) international negotiating.\n* Commercially succesful in both primary and secondary financial markets.\n* Skilled in employing cross and deep selling strategies.\n* Clear affinity with IT in an international banking environment.\n* I enjoy coaching young people.",
